Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Backend/API Engineer, Money as a Service* role with *Stripe*. I bring over three years of software engineering experience building backend systems and APIs, along with a Master of Science in Computer Science from Pace University.

At Sperse, I scoped, designed, built, and maintained *ergonomic APIs* and backend services in an MCP layer that translated natural-language intents into safe, validated tool calls across *1000+ platform endpoints*. I also built production observability with *Langfuse* and *LangSmith* to diagnose critical production issues across services, and partnered with cross-functional teams in a distributed and hybrid team model to improve engineering standards, tooling, and processes. At Qualitest, I designed a cloud-agnostic storage service using *Python*, *PostgreSQL*, and *Redis* across *Google Cloud Storage*, *S3*, and *MinIO*, and developed *AWS Step Functions* workflows with *AWS Lambda* timeout controls for long-running imports. These experiences map directly to building and maintaining reliable APIs, services, and large-scale systems for money movement.

I would also bring strong mentorship and technical communication to MaaS. As an AI Researcher at Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I built repeatable training pipelines for *StyleGAN* and *Stable Diffusion* with *CUDA*, *PyTorch*, and *LoRA* on an HPC cluster, and mentored *+50* students through workshops on CUDA, Mojo, and AI agent systems with *LangChain*, *LangGraph*, and *LangSmith*. This experience prepared me to help peers grow while keeping technical rigor high.

Stripe’s mission to build financial infrastructure for ambitious companies and grow the GDP of the internet strongly resonates with me. I am especially aligned with your values of *Users first* and *Collaborate egolessly*, and I would be excited to contribute to Stripe’s goal of making internet payments and money movement more reliable and accessible at global scale. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml.

